meta {
  name: 5 Documents - ingest lab PDF
  type: http
  seq: 5
}

post {
  url: {{baseUrl}}/documents
  body: multipartForm
}

headers {
  X-Clinician-Id: {{clinician}}
}

body:multipart-form {
  patient_id: {{patient}}
  doc_type: lab_pdf
  file: @file(../fixtures/sample_lab_report.pdf)
}

docs {
  Week 2 multimodal ingestion. Attach ANY lab-report PDF or photo - Claude
  vision reads the actual document; no fixture is required. (A synthetic
  sample can be generated locally with fixtures/make_sample_lab.py.)

  -> 200 with doc_type=lab_pdf, result_count, and results[]: each extracted
  value carries test_name, unit, reference_range, abnormal_flag, confidence,
  a verbatim-quote citation anchored to document_id, and a page bounding box
  where the model located it. Strict schema: a hallucinated field fails
  validation and never enters the record. Re-uploading the same file is
  idempotent (same document_id).
}
